snippet: The Bush family, a dynasty that defined Republicanism for decades, clashed on Monday with the new and irreverent face of the party, Donald J. Trump, in one of the most powerful collisions of the primary campaign so far.
abstract: Bush family dynasty, which defined Republicanism for many years, vigorously and vividly clashes with presidential candidate Donald J Trump; Jeb Bush, under mounting pressure in South Carolina, brings brother George W Bush and former first lady Laura Bush to swipe at Trump after he charges nation was not safe during George W Bush's presidency.

byline.original: By ASHLEY PARKER and MAGGIE HABERMAN
byline.contributor: Ashley Parker reported from North Charleston, and Maggie Haberman from New York.

lead_paragraph: The Bush family, a dynasty that defined Republicanism for decades, clashed on Monday with the new and irreverent face of the party, Donald J. Trump, in one of the most powerful collisions of the primary campaign so far.

headline.main: Jeb Bush, With Assist From George, Goes After Donald Trump
